  "ambience": "swamp",
  "intro": [
    {
      "title": "Mire Hold",
      "lines": [
        "The mire ate the old causeway whole. What is left are two threads of mud across the black water — and a reed island the fog has not yet claimed.",
        "Cross to the redoubt and touch the core; the night will not fall until you do. Then there is no leaving.",
        "Bog spitters squat the bridges and spit rot onto the mud. The peat itself breathes poison. Hold the island three nights — two of them under a blood moon."
      ],
      "art": "siege"
    }
  ],
  "outro": [
    {
      "title": "The Reeds Still Stand",
      "lines": [
        "Three dawns, and the island is still above the water. The fog draws back from a hold that would not drown.",
        "Bog and blood moon both spent themselves on the reeds. Stone could not have done better."
      ],
      "art": "dawn"
    }
  ],
